-- Harmony Gold Gains After Profit Beats Estimates
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2012-02-06T07:48:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/harmony-gold-gains-after-profit-beats-estimates-correct-.html
(Corrects period of gain in headline and first paragraph.)  Harmony Gold Mining Co. gained the
most in more than two months after reporting second-quarter
profit that beat estimates.  The stock jumped as much as 4.9 percent, its biggest
intraday increase since Nov. 30, to 97.64 rand and was trading
at 97.11 rand as of 9:05 a.m. in Johannesburg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
